me span from Greek Antiquity to Byzantium.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aGreek literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aAeschylus. 4aBacchae. 4aChristus Patiens. 4aClassical Reception.  aAeschylus' 'Dionysiac' tetralogies.  aBacchae.  aChristus Patiens.  aClassical reception.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishz978311099291508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022z9783110992878oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831107644990 cprintz978311076434540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076441340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110764413423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110764413/original  a978-3-11-099291-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022